cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.SC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper focuses on program slicing, which is a technique used in programming languages to extract parts of a program that are relevant to a particular computation. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses an approach to building programs that can explain their work, which is relevant to software engineering. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper presents proofs of correctness and optimality of the approach, which is related to logic in computer science. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory): The paper uses a lattice-based approach to program slicing, which is related to formal languages and automata theory. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation): The paper discusses a technique for symbolic computation (program slicing) in functional programs.
